Xinhua Commentary: Making Excellent Returning Migrant Workers a New Force for Rural Revitalization - Xinhua News Agency
Talent is the key to rural revitalization.
Where can I find talent?
The group of outstanding returning migrant workers is an indispensable new force.
Hai Chunzuo, Xinhua News Agency
(Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26) Topic: Make outstanding returning migrant workers a new force for rural revitalization
The 34-year-old Zhang Xiong family is in Orchard Village, Meishan City, Sichuan. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a salary of tens of thousands a month and returned home to start a business.
After several years of hard work, he now runs a grape-growing family farm with an annual income of more than one million yuan, has become a well-known rich leader, and has also been selected into the team of the " two committees " of the village.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support and benefit farmers, such as poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return home to start their own businesses, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a populous province in western China and a major labor-exporting province, has implemented the " Excellent Migrant Workers Return Training Project. " In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village Party branch secretaries were generated from among the outstanding migrant workers, cultivating 61,000 village reserve forces and developing more than 20,000 Party members, thus providing a strong guarantee for winning the fight against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
Well-off is not well-off, the key depends on the villagers.
Since the reform and opening-up, a large number of young and middle-aged rural workers have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively, it has also led to the emergence of " hollowing out " in rural areas to varying degrees. In particular, rural grass-roots organizations have been weakened, and the secretary of the village Party branch and the team of Party members have shown the characteristics of " one old and one low, " namely, the age is old, the educational qualifications are low, the team of leaders of the village Party organization is not strong and the problem is outstanding.
If rural talents and other factors have been flowing one way to the city, and the countryside is in a state of " blood loss " and " anemia " for a long time, revitalization is an empty word.
Attract back those rural migrant workers who have the ability, consciousness and ambition to serve their hometown, guide them to return home and start their own businesses to become rich leaders, train them to become Party members and village cadres on the basis of merit, and enrich the ranks of grass-roots cadres. This is the fundamental solution to the lack of contact between the ranks of rural Party members and grass-roots Party organizations.
Excellent migrant workers can be brought back, and they should be allowed to stay and do well.
In recent years, Sichuan has started by paying close attention to the Party building of rural migrant workers and, on the basis of strict selection criteria, has established institutional mechanisms such as targeted referral, service guarantee, training and ability enhancement, selection and use of outstanding rural migrant workers, so that they can improve their ability, have job security, have expectations in life, truly take root in rural areas, and officials have a sense of achievement in starting a business.
This year is the final year of the decisive battle against poverty. Talent is the key factor to make a good connection between poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Governments at all levels of the Party should attach great importance to this group of outstanding returning migrant workers and, through comprehensive measures, turn them into a task force and a new force that can stay, fight and take away, so as to provide a strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty alleviation, prosperity, development and revitalization.
