Beijing's natural ecology continues to improve to attract more than 500 species of wildlife city " settlement " - New Network
2020-07-26 05: 03: 17 Source: Beijing Youth Daily Author: Wang Sishuo Executive Editor: Wang Sishuo
The natural ecology of the capital continues to improve to attract wildlife cities to " settle "
There are more than 500 species of wild animals in Beijing
Xinhua News (Reporter Wang Bin) Beijing Youth Daily reporter learned from the Municipal Landscaping Bureau that in recent years, with the continuous improvement of the natural and ecological environment of the capital, the variety and number of wild animals have also continued to increase.
At present, the number of terrestrial vertebrate wildlife living in Beijing has increased to more than 500 species, including national-level protected animals such as brown horse chicken and black stork, as well as national-level protected animals such as gazelle, swan, grey crane and mandarin duck.
Whether the urban forests planted everywhere in the Second Ring, or the small and micro wetlands embedded between buildings, not only bring the wild interest of nature to the citizens of the capital, but also attract wild animals to " settle " in the city.
In the middle of summer, the Songshan National Nature Reserve, located in the Yanshan Mountains in the northwest of Yanqing District, is full of vitality.
A raccoon played leisurely by the mountain stream, while two badgers quarreled with each other.
In retrospect, a wild boar could not resist the " scratch " on his body and was rubbing hard against the bark. Hu Qiaoli, director of the administrative department of Songshan National Nature Reserve, said that as of the end of 2019, in this green sea with a total area of more than 6,200 hectares, there were 178 species of wild animals, including national-level protected animals gold carving, national-level protected animals spoon chicken and gazelle, and nearly one third of the city's wildlife species can be seen here.
" In Songshan, wild animals are the real' masters', and our staff can only be regarded as people's' bodyguards' at best. "
Hu Qiaoli said that in order to understand the situation of wild flora and fauna in the protected area on the ground, more than 30 professional patrol members patrol along 16 carefully formulated protection routes every day, and there will be a " big circle " every month, going through almost the entire protected area in a full day.
" During the inspection, we should not only check and record biodiversity, but also check and install artificial nests, rescue injured wild animals, install infrared cameras in the field, and so on. "
More than 200 infrared cameras have been installed in the Songshan National Nature Reserve to record the living conditions of wildlife in the forest.
Hu Qiaoli introduced that with the continuous enrichment of biodiversity in the protected areas in recent years, more and more wild animals appear in the camera, leopard cats, dragons and pig badgers have become " permanent guests, " and the " mirror rate " of the gazelle, a second-class national protected animal, is also increasing.
Zhang Zhiming, Director of the Wildlife and Wetland Protection Department of the Beijing Parks and Landscaping Bureau, said that the number of terrestrial vertebrate wildlife in Beijing has increased from 461 species in 1994 to more than 500 at present, and the species and number of wildlife in Beijing have continuously increased in recent years.
Wild animals are becoming more and more common in cities, which is closely related to the continuous upgrading of greening in the capital city in recent years.
In particular, the new round of afforestation construction of one million mu, which began in 2018, proposes to reshape the urban ecological environment, enhance the ecological function of forestland and green areas, and highlight the concept of " near nature. "
The planning strives to achieve interconnection and interaction with the surrounding green areas, making it easier for wild animals to " visit relatives and friends, " and the trees planted are also favorite honey and food plants for animals.
Black Land " Seeds " Agricultural Modernization - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Harbin, July 26, Topic: Black land " grows " out of agricultural modernization
In the middle of summer, two spraying planes flew over a million mu high-yield demonstration field in the second operation station of the fifth management area of Friendship Farm, forming two white lines. The big words " the first field in the world " planted with black rice seedlings in the green fields stand out.
The station master Kong Lingqiang said that this kind of aircraft can spray medicine on 6,000 acres of arable land a day. The efficiency is about eight times that of unmanned aerial vehicles and hundreds of times that of artificial personnel.
This farm is located in Friendship County, Heilongjiang Province, the largest grain-producing province in China. From the sound of rice cutting in the past to the sound of " rumbling " today, Chinese traditional farming and farms have been transformed in this black soil belt.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in the modern agricultural production of Friendship Farm.
Kong Lingqiang introduced that, on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve accurate fertilization, reduce agricultural input and reduce pollution; on the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the standardized operation level of agricultural machinery in the field.
During this year's rice production, the farm expanded the operating area of satellite navigation unmanned transplanting technology from 3,000 mu last year to 30,000 mu.
This technology makes seedling planting more uniform, maximizes the utilization of sunlight and arable land resources, and saves labor costs of 16 yuan per acre.
The farm experimented with new technologies such as informatization and intelligence in agricultural production, forming the largest group of agricultural machinery in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, the total number of farm agricultural machinery is 49,000 units (pieces), and the rate of comprehensive mechanization in the field is 99.8%.
Agricultural machinery operation to achieve GPS satellite navigation 100%, dry field precision seeding 100%, dry field high-horsepower locomotive operation 100%.
" Green agriculture, smart agriculture and digital agriculture are the exploration direction of agricultural modernization. "
Friendship farm director Liu Hualien said.
The key to agricultural modernization lies in scientific and technological progress.
Agricultural reclamation in Heilongjiang, represented by farms, has played a demonstration and leading role in modern large-scale agriculture " aircraft carrier " in recent years, and has initially established a modern agro-industrial system dominated by large-scale cultivation, standardized production and industrial management.
On the outskirts of Friendship County, there is an agricultural machinery exhibition park covering an area of 350,000 square meters.
There is a concentrated exhibition of more than 140 agricultural tools that have been introduced and used in agricultural reclamation in Heilongjiang over the years.
These agricultural tools and farms witnessed the development process of China's agricultural modernization.
Xie Xiaojia for everyone - Anhui Hefei Jiangkou River Union Wei mass transfer hit - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Hefei, July 26, Topic: Xie Xiaojia for everyone - Hefei, Anhui Province, Jiangkou River Lianwei mass transfer hit
Xinhua News Agency reporters Chen Shangying, Wang Liwu and Liu Xiacun
At 4: 00 pm on July 25, Fu Kunbao, wearing rubber shoes covered with mud, went from the front room to the back room, and his wife Zhou Yan were busy picking up things back and forth.
" When I received the call from the village cadres to transfer, I was still collecting grass in the field. "
Fu Kunbao said that he had transferred 60 acres of land and planted rice. At present, he is growing well. " He also took medicine yesterday, and the tools have not been cleaned up. "
Fu Kunbao pointed to the pesticide sprayer placed in the corner. " No one wants his home to be flooded. Leave his family for everyone. "
In order to cope with the persistent high water level pressure and possible heavy rainfall in Chaohu Lake, Hefei, Anhui Province, is preparing to use the Jiangkou River Lianwei flood water storage facility, where Fu Kunbao's family is located, on the 26th.
Jiangkou River Union Wei is located in Feixi County, adjacent to the Chaohu dike.
In Wei, thousands of villagers involved in Yandian Township and Sanhe Town need to be relocated.
As of 16: 00 on the 25th, the water level of Chaohu Lake, China's fifth largest freshwater lake, remained at a high level of 13.2 meters, exceeding the guaranteed water level of 0.7 meters.
Fu Kunbao's kitchen was clean, with a pot of pumpkin dishes on the table, eggs and some brine dishes in the refrigerator.
" I didn't expect to move. The water in the Jiangkou River looks good at present. "
Zhou Yan said that the home is a bungalow, and some large objects have not yet decided where to put them.
" Clean up the valuable items first, and large items such as refrigerators and televisions can be temporarily placed in the homes of high-lying neighbors or relatives. "
The village cadre Wang Li steadily gave advice to Fu Kunbao.
Wang Liweng is responsible for the transfer and resettlement of 13 villagers, one household notice to confirm each person's resettlement plan.
The nearest settlement to Fu Kunbao's home is Su Xiaoxue, Yandian Township, about 2 kilometers away.
In addition to the large pieces, Fu and his wife had a headache with more than 1,000 kilograms of grain and some newly bought furniture.
" The food is ready to be dragged to relatives' homes, and the furniture cannot be moved. "
After a discussion, the couple put a stool under the newly bought bed and raised the bed by about half a meter.
At 6 p.m., Fu Kunbao began to use a tricycle to carry things to the homes of relatives. Zhou Yan continued to clean up at home.
At 11 o'clock in the evening, the couple looked back and forth at home, pulled up the electric gate, ready to go to the settlement.
" I hope the water will come back soon. "
Fu Kunbao said.
At 9: 30 am on July 26, the reporter saw at the Jiangkou River Lianwei scene that the local area had made all preparations before dividing the flood.
