(China's Poverty Reduction Story) " Sealing up to Jiangnan " in pursuit of the poetic " Yellow River Dream "
China News Service, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) " Jiuqu Yellow River thousands of miles of sand, waves and wind from the horizon. "
The Yellow River, which has aroused the pride of countless scholars, has given birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Today, Ningxia, which has the reputation of " Shangjiang Jiangnan, " is adhering to the concept of " ecological priority and green development " and pursuing the poetic " Yellow River Dream. "
River Shimizu Show's " Bibo Dream "
" The Yellow River is rich in Ningxia. " The Yellow River flows through Ningxia for 397 kilometers and is the " mother river " for raising one side.
However, with the rapid progress of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization, management and protection of rivers and lakes are unbalanced, and disturbances such as excessive sewage discharge, surrounding lakes to build fields, and encroaching on water areas have become prominent, leading to black and stinking water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the diverse restoration of water ecology and making efforts to return the Yellow River to show the river clear.
Water management should start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, by adopting the method of " bidding + pollution control + strict control, " all sewage from industrial parks has been centrally treated, all urban sewage treatment plants have achieved Class A standard discharge, black and stinking water bodies in built-up urban areas have been basically eliminated, and the third batch of black and stinking water demonstration cities in China has been successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake long system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake long responsibility system in districts, cities and villages, and river and lake long river crossing has become the norm.
64-year-old Gu Jincheng, who lives in a village near the Yellow River, witnessed the changes of the Yellow River: " There was a foul smell in the water before, but the foul smell disappeared after remediation. "
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better and his life is more comfortable. Now he often goes for a walk along the Yellow River with his family to feel the blue water and blue sky.
The " Wetland Dream " of Sha Gu Xiang Collection
Flying birds, green trees, walkways, turquoise water... The beauty of Fan Zhongyan's " Sand Gull Xiang Collection " has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia and has formed a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands and swamp wetlands along the way, which plays an important role in promoting the rational utilization of water resources and water ecological balance. It has also become an important international migration channel for birds.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have cumulatively invested about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, Yinchuan has a wetland area of 192 million hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and swamp wetlands, five national wetland parks, one national urban wetland park, six autonomous region-level wetland parks and eight municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds. " The remnant gull is an endangered bird. There are only more than 20,000 birds in the world, of which more than 2,000 live in the Yinchuan wetland. "
Meanwhile, in accordance with the law, Ningxia has delineated a 500-meter red line for the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River, stipulating that no unit or individual may carry out development, construction and business activities within the scope of protection except for public welfare projects.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of the Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through the control of pollution sources, the comprehensive management of river and lake ecology and the construction of terminal wetlands, the water quality of the nine main yellow drainage ditches in Ningxia has now reached 100% of the Class IV standard. " Now the water is clear, the fish swim and the flowers bloom. "
Pu Huiminsheng's " Drinking Water Dream "
Yinchuan City, Ningxia, once had the title of " embarrassment ": the only city along the Yellow River that " keeps the Yellow River short of water. "
Since 2010, Yinchuan has been facing a persistent problem of water shortage during the peak summer season. The " pain of water shortage " in the past decade has become a painful summer experience for many high-rise residents. However, under the current situation that the major water sources are at the limit of overmining and a large area of groundwater overmining funnel has been formed underground in urban areas, water-based water shortage has become a difficult problem besetting Yinchuan.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking the purified Yellow River has become a good solution to the drinking water problems of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of the Yinchuan City Water Bureau, introduced that in order to improve the living and production water demand of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia started the water supply project on the urban and rural western line of the Yinchuan metropolitan area in due time, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River.
" On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially provided water to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank the Yellow River. "
Ding Ming said that the water conservancy department of Yinchuan will give overall consideration to the transformation of the regional integration of rural drinking water and urban water supply. " In the next step, we will integrate all the rural decentralized water supply points into the Western Line water supply project, and it is expected to basically realize the urban-rural integrated water supply in Yinchuan by the end of this year. "
