House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell announced last week that people could come to the United States Capitol on Monday and Tuesday to pay tribute to Lewis.
A public event in memory of Lewis will be held outdoors due to the COVID-19 pandemic.
Shenzhen Public Consultation on the Introduction of Health Regulations - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (reporters Mao Siqian and Bai Yu) encourages residents to do frequent medical check-ups and detect problems as soon as possible; prohibits the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; establishes an online game health review system; and employers should have full-time and part-time health management personnel... Recently, the Health Regulations of the Shenzhen Special Economic Zone (Consultation Draft) was officially released, and Shenzhen residents will have their own " health law. "
In order to encourage residents to do medical check-ups frequently and detect problems early, the above-mentioned consultation draft proposes that health and health departments should draw up a basic catalogue of health check-up items according to different ages, occupations and other factors.
The health check-up expenses falling within the scope of the basic catalogue of health check-up items shall be paid by the overall social medical insurance fund according to the standard of once per person per year.
The consultation draft makes it clear that the employing unit should rationally allocate human resources, arrange rest time for employees, implement a rotational rest system for employees with heavy mental and physical workloads, avoid excessive loss of human function or physical and mental health injury to employees' health, and strictly implement the paid leave system for employees.
In addition, employers should have full-time and part-time health management personnel and organize regular health check-ups of employees.
With regard to the physical and mental health of minors, the consultation draft proposes that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited. At the same time, the location of the sale of alcoholic beverages is restricted. Those who violate the regulations will be ordered by the market supervision and administration department to make corrections and impose a fine of 30,000 yuan.
In addition to " prohibition of alcohol, " minors should also " exercise more. "
According to the requirements of the consultation draft, schools should arrange students' sports activities for more than one hour every day.
With regard to online games, the departments of public security, culture, radio, television, tourism, sports, network supervision, health and health should improve the health supervision system of Internet service business places, establish a health review system for online games, and create a good communication space and communication culture for promoting the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the consultation draft also proposed that influenza patients must wear face masks in and out of public places, and that medical and health institutions should be fined 20,000 yuan for disclosing patients' privacy without consent.
It is noteworthy that, in addition to the physical and mental health of the residents, the consultation draft also requires that all departments in Shenzhen should assess the impact of the implementation of public policies on the health of the population before formulating plans and normative documents related to urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and eco-environmental protection, and the development of the biomedical industry, as well as the approval of major construction projects and the implementation of major public service projects.
If it has not been assessed or will have a more serious adverse impact on urban public health or the health of residents, it shall not be formulated or approved for implementation.
