Koxili Tibetan antelope enters the migration season - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, July 25 (Reporter Wang Jinjin) The reporter learned from the Wudaoliang Protection Station of the Kao Xili Management Office of the Changyuan Park of the Sanjiangyuan National Park Administration that the monitoring showed that the Tibetan antelope who had migrated to the Zhuonai Lake area in the hinterland of Kao Xili were gradually ending giving birth and began to bring their babies back to their original habitat.
Surveillance footage near the Wudaoliang Protection Station shows that on July 25, about 40 female Tibetan antelope and three Tibetan antelope cubs passed through 3002 km of the Qinghai-Tibet Highway and the Wudao Liangbei Bridge of the Qinghai-Tibet Railway. The Tibetan antelope has begun to move back.
According to experts, in recent years, the number of Tibetan antelope cubs in the migrating sheep accounted for one-quarter to one-fifth of the total Tibetan antelope population.
Lian Xinming, an associate researcher at the Institute of Northwest Plateau Biology of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, said, " At the beginning of the migration, the Tibetan antelope faces a higher risk of being hunted, so the number of cubs in the sheep will be relatively small, and there may even be no cubs. "
According to the statistics of the Koxili Management Office of the Changyuan Park of the Sanjiangyuan National Park Administration, the overall number of Tibetan antelope migrations is increasing year by year, and the number of Tibetan antelope migrations in 2019 was 4,860, an increase of 338 over 2018.
Lian Xinming said: " It is expected that the return migration of Tibetan antelope will end in early September this year, and the number of Tibetan antelope is still expected to continue to increase. "
The Tibetan antelope is a protected animal at the national level.
At the end of May every year, Tibetan antelopes from Sanjiangyuan in Qinghai, Qiangtang in Tibet and AlJinshan in Xinjiang go to Zhuonai Lake in the hinterland of Koxili to lay lambs.
Wu Xiaomin, an expert on the protection of the Tibetan antelope in China and a researcher at the Shaanxi Provincial Zoological Research Institute (Northwest Institute of Endangered Animals), said, " The migration of the Tibetan antelope is a process in which the female Tibetan antelope returns to their habitat with their cubs after giving birth. At first, the returning population leaving the breeding site is relatively large, but then the Tibetan antelope will return to their respective habitats according to different geographical populations and along different paths. "
In order to ensure the safe relocation of the Tibetan antelope population, the reporter learned that the Koxili Management Office of Changyuan Park of the Sanjiangyuan National Park Administration has arranged staff to continuously carry out video monitoring and district patrols in the main relocation areas.
If a herd of Tibetan antelope is found trying to cross the road, the mountain patrol team will carry out temporary traffic control at the first time to allow the sheep to pass safely through the wildlife passage, so as to ensure that they are subject to as little human interference as possible on the way back.
So, how to relieve the heat in daily life?
Experts suggest that going out in the summer should try to avoid the hot time, and it is best not to walk or work in the hot sun around noon, because the sun is strongest during this period and the possibility of heatstroke is higher.
If you have to go out at this time, you must do a good job of protection, such as playing a parasol, wearing a sun cap, wearing sunglasses, conditionally, it is best to apply sunscreen to sunscreen.
Clothes should try to choose cotton, hemp and silk textures with light color and good air permeability, and wear less chemical fiber clothing, so as to avoid timely heat dissipation when sweating a lot, causing heatstroke.
In hot and sultry weather, you should prepare enough water to drink, drink it in time, and do not wait until you are thirsty to drink water, because once you feel thirsty means that your body is already short of water, drink water from 150 ml to 200 ml each time, drink warm water, do not drink ice water.
According to the temperature, ordinary people drink 1.5 to 2 liters of water per day, while high-temperature workers drink 3 to 5 liters of water per day.
Sweat more can be appropriate to supplement some salt water to make up for the loss of salt due to sweat.
In addition, the human body is prone to potassium deficiency in summer, which makes people feel tired and tired. Potassium-containing tea is an excellent summer drink.
Eat more fruits and vegetables with high water content in summer, such as lettuce, cucumbers and tomatoes; fresh fruits, such as peaches, apricots, watermelon and melon, have a water content of 80% to 90%, which can be used to replenish water; dairy products can both replenish water and meet the nutritional needs of the body.
In addition, people working in a high temperature environment should properly supplement drinks containing elements such as potassium and magnesium.
Summer days and nights are short, the temperature is high, human metabolism is strong, consumption is also large, easy to feel fatigue.
Adequate sleep can relax the brain and body systems, which is not only conducive to work and study, but also a measure to prevent heatstroke.
Experts say that the best time to go to bed is from 22: 00 to 23: 00 and the best time to get up is from 5: 30 to 6: 30.
When sleeping, be careful not to lie under the air-conditioning outlet and electric fan, so as not to suffer from air-conditioning disease and hot cold.
