Dalian: No new locally confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia: 24 new cases of asymptomatic infection - Xinhua News
Xinhua News Agency, Dalian, July 25 (reporters Cai Zhongjun and Cui Shihao) Dalian announced on July 25 that there were no new locally confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia in Dalian from 15: 00 on July 24 to 14: 00 on July 25, with 24 new cases of asymptomatic infection and no new suspected cases.
From July 22 to 14: 00 on July 25, the city reported a total of 12 locally confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia, all of which were centrally isolated for treatment at the Sixth People's Hospital in Dalian.
Zhao Lian, deputy director of the Dalian Municipal Board of Health and Health, said that according to the epidemic situation, Dalian organized the medical staff of the city's tertiary hospitals to enter the street communities, opened more than 600 sampling points in Dalian Bay, Workers' Village, along the light rail and some key areas of Jinpu New District, made every effort to promote the nucleic acid screening of personnel, and dispatched nearly 2,000 medical staff to carry out nucleic acid detection and sampling every day.
By 14: 00 on July 25, the city had sampled more than 210,000 people.
Of the current 12 confirmed cases in Dalian, 10 were employees of Dalian Kaiyang World Seafood Co., Ltd.; of the 54 cases of asymptomatic infection, 46 were employees of the company and their relatives; of all the nucleic acid test positive cases, the proportion of employees of the enterprise and their relatives reached 85%.
After the judgment, Dalian decided to strengthen strict control over the close contacts and close contacts of all employees of Dalian Kaiyang World Seafood Co., Ltd., and to implement centralized isolation medical observation for 14 days and at least two nucleic acid tests.
At the same time, Dalian decided to further expand the scope of personnel implementing centralized isolation medical observation, and to carry out 14-day centralized isolation medical observation and at least 2 nucleic acid tests for close contacts and close contacts of persons with positive nucleic acid tests (including cases and asymptomatic infections).
Dalian Airport and Dalian Railway Station issued a notice on the 25th day that the city's personnel do not need to stay connected in principle. If they really need to leave, they must hold a certificate of negative nucleic acid test within 7 days. The Dalian Bus Terminal will suspend ticket sales on all routes in the city from 12 o'clock on the 25th, and the specific recovery time will be announced.
Brazilian study shows that hydroxycloquinine is ineffective in the treatment of mild and moderate COVID-19 pneumonia.
Recently, a Brazilian study showed that hydroxychloroquine was ineffective in patients with mild and moderate COVID-19 pneumonia.
The study was published in the New England Journal of Medicine.
Researchers in Pakistan divided 667 patients from 55 hospitals across the country into three groups and conducted clinical trials. They mainly compared the therapeutic effects of hydroxychloroquine alone or in combination with other antibiotics azithromycin, and analyzed whether it could help improve the condition of patients with mild and moderate COVID-19 pneumonia.
The results show that hydroxychloroquine not only has no therapeutic effect, but may have damaging side effects on organs.
The study was carried out jointly by several authoritative Brazilian hospitals such as Hospital Israel Albert Einstein, Heart Hospital (HCor), Hospital Sírio-Libanês, the Brazilian Clinical Institute (BCRI) and the Brazilian Intensive Care Research Network (BRICNet).
On the 25th local time, Brazilian President Bossonaro announced through social networking platforms that the fourth nucleic acid test result was negative.
Bossonaro has been taking hydroxychloroquine during the infection and has been actively promoted several times.
