Four departments carry out a new round of app governance to protect personal information security - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 25 (reporters Yu Junjie and Chen Aiping) The reporter learned from the Cyberspace Administration of China on July 25 that the management of the illegal collection and use of personal information by apps in 2020 was officially launched recently, focusing on cracking down on strong issues such as the unauthorized uploading of personal information in the background of the app.
It is reported that this round of app governance work was carried out jointly by four departments of the State Cyberspace Administration, the Ministry of Industry, the Ministry of Public Security and the State Market Supervision Administration.
According to reports, the special governance working group composed of four departments accepted more than 12,000 effective reports from netizens last year, verified more than 2,300 apps, and took punitive measures such as public exposure, interview and removal of 260 apps with large users and outstanding problems.
According to the relevant person in charge of the State Cyberspace Administration, the number of apps currently exceeds 5 million, and the problem of illegal collection and use of personal information has not yet been fundamentally solved.
The governance work in 2020 will be further intensified, and the scope of governance will be further expanded to include SDKs (software development kits) and applets on the basis of app verification.
It is reported that the working group will conduct thematic studies and in-depth tests on issues such as the irregular collection and use of personal biometric information and the abuse of sensitive rights by apps, focusing on the abuse of background rights such as recording and taking photos.
According to the circumstances of the problem and the seriousness of the consequences, the working group will impose penalties such as interviews, warnings, removal from shelves and fines in accordance with laws and regulations, so as to effectively deter violations of laws and regulations.
It is understood that the working group plans to formulate and issue guidelines for the audit management of app stores for the collection and use of personal information by apps, guide and urge app stores to do a good job in the audit of apps before they go online, and strictly enter the port.
In addition, the working group will also release free technical tools to guide small and medium-sized enterprises in conducting self-test assessments and improve the legal compliance of the collection and use of personal information by small and medium-sized enterprises.
