Hao Yusheng, chief representative of NASDAQ China: Now is the best time for Chinese companies to IPO in the US
Zhang Bin, a reporter from the Economic Observer Network, because of the coffee fraud incident, the US market has imposed stricter supervision on CPC stocks, coupled with the long-term pressure on valuation and the pressure on CPC stocks listed in the United States, NetEase, Jingdong and other CPC stocks have recently started their journey back to Hong Kong for listing.
And the recent shell, ideal car and other companies, the enthusiasm for listing in the United States is high.
Under the epidemic and the stock crisis, is this the best time for Chinese companies to list in the United States?
" With regard to the recent IPO cases and the subsequent listing of companies in the United States, the IPO in the United States has not been affected in essence. Instead, the market is very good now, and even now this time is the best time for Chinese companies to IPO in the United States in the past 10 years. "
Hao Yusheng, China's chief representative of the NASDAQ Stock Exchange, said at the " 2020 Listed Companies Leaders Summit " hosted by Snowball.
In April this year, the US Securities and Futures Commission (SEC) and the US Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (PCAOB) issued a " Statement on Audit Quality and the Important Role of Regulatory Access to Audit and Other International Information - A Discussion on the Current Challenges of Access to Information for US Listed Companies with Large Business in China. "
The statement said that despite the significant increase in international cooperation and coordination in recent years, the US regulatory authorities still have problems in obtaining information, and the SEC and PCAOB still face legal and practical challenges. In contrast to the document, the PCAOB website provides a detailed list of listed companies that have encountered auditing obstacles and their auditing institutions, with a large number of medium-sized stock companies listed.
In addition, in May this year, the US Senate passed the Foreign Corporate Accountability Act, which imposes additional information disclosure requirements on the listing of foreign companies in the US.
In Hao Yusheng's view, the Zhongbao stock crisis did not affect the appetite of investors.
" When the news first came out, it caused panic among everyone, and everyone was asking whether they could go to the US for listing in the future, but later we found out that these issues were not a matter for investors. Investors might ask these questions during the recent US IPO roadshow, or even become a standardized issue, but this was not taken by investors as an important factor in investing in or not investing in a Chinese company.
It is suggested that everyone should try to look at the current situation with an ordinary mind.
Of course, this may appear to be the most serious situation in the past two years, but in terms of investors' appetite, it has not been affected.
So the upsurge of IPOs in the US will continue between now and the end of this year or before the US general election. "
On May 9 this year, Jinshan Cloud was officially listed on the NASDAQ, becoming the first Chinese company to make an IPO in the United States after the outbreak.
" The listing of Jinshan Cloud gives great confidence to the Chinese companies that are preparing for an IPO. "
Hao Yusheng said.
The overall stock data report released by Snowball in the first half of 2020 shows that in the first half of this year, a total of 20 Chinese companies made IPOs in the United States, an increase of 17.6% compared to the same period last year. Judging from the total initial fund-raising, 20 companies raised a total of 2.725 billion yuan, an increase of more than 52.4% compared to the same period last year. In terms of industry distribution, the number of IPOs in the healthcare industry was outstanding in the first half of this year, an increase of 100% compared to the same period last year.
According to Hao Yusheng, the Chinese companies that IPO in the United States in the first half of this year are of high quality, and high-quality companies with strong fundamentals and growth will be more favored by investors.
In the short, medium and long term, Hao Yusheng continues to be optimistic about Ming China's IPO in the United States.
" In the short term, the upsurge of IPOs in the United States is still going on; in the medium term, Chinese companies have more choices, A shares, Hong Kong stocks and U.S. stocks, and everyone will take the US election and China-US relations as consideration factors in market choice and timing; in the long run, everything will return to normal, and market fluctuations are cyclical, with both political and economic cycles, and will eventually return to the normal stage, and the stock market has always been volatile. "
Hao Yusheng also said, " There are many uncertain factors this year, but for high-quality companies, whether the market is good or bad, as long as they are solid and have growth that investors can see, other factors are relatively secondary. Investors need to invest in excellent Chinese companies. "
Xinhua News, Beijing, July 26 (Reporter Gao Kai) On the evening of July 25, the " Dance of Life " of the NCPA concert series " Sounds like summer flowers " was performed simultaneously online and offline as scheduled. Conductor Yang and pianist Zhang Haochen cooperated with the NCPA Orchestra to perform Rachmaninov's " Second Piano Concerto " and " Symphonic Dance. "
