Chongqing Wulong landslide formed a barrier lake local emergency transfer of more than 500 people - Xinhua News
Xinhua News Agency, Chongqing, July 26 (reporters Zhou Wenchong and Ke Gaoyang) The reporter learned from the Chongqing Wulong District Government on July 26 that the heavy rainfall caused landslides and formed a barrier lake, and more than 500 people were evacuated urgently.
Under the influence of continuous rainfall, since July 22, there has been a large area of slip deformation in the soil cracking at the back edge of the Zhongbao landslide in Zhongtai Group, Liujing Village, Land Township, Wulong District, and the slope fell into the tributary of the Wujiang River along the Cang River.
On the 25th, a process of heavy rainfall occurred in the area, and the landslide further expanded, which disrupted the passage of village roads and completely blocked the passage along the Cang River, forming a barrier lake with a water level of 13 meters in front of the dam and a storage capacity of about 420,000 cubic meters.
According to on-site survey and monitoring, the volume of the landslide is about 1.3 million cubic meters. At present, the landslide is still in an unstable state, with sporadic rock falls, there has been a dam overflow in the weir lake, and there is a risk of breakage, posing a threat to the downstream power station and the town.
After the danger occurred, the local government organized the evacuation of residents along the river overnight and urgently transferred the people to safety.
At present, 162 households and 520 people in the dangerous area have been evacuated, and the disposal of the barrier lake is still under way.
