Xinhua News Agency, Kuala Lumpur, July 25 (Reporter Lin Hao) A videoconference of trade ministers of Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) members was held on July 25. The meeting pledged to work to reduce the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on the regional economy and accelerate the realization of a resilient, sustainable and inclusive regional economic recovery.
