Xiamen, July 26 (Yang Fushan Zhang Shushan Xu Jingyi) China's famous vascular surgery center, Shanghai Changhai Hospital of Naval Military Medical University, signed a contract for vascular surgery with Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University on July 25 to jointly set up a collaboration center to promote exchanges and cooperation between the two sides in the specialty of vascular surgery, especially in the field of acute and severe aorta.
Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University said that after the vascular surgery of the two hospitals has officially formed a collaborative unit, it will carry out remote consultation, formulate a treatment plan through real-time online consultation with Changhai Hospital, select personnel for further training, and jointly carry out surgical technical exchanges, teaching and room inspection on a weekly basis. For complex cases, Changhai experts can be invited to the hospital to perform surgery according to the needs of patients, so that patients in southwest Fujian can enjoy the top medical resources in China without the province.
The two hospitals will also jointly carry out scientific research on surgical innovation, popularization of aortic diseases and early screening.
A special seminar on aorta hosted by the Beijing Health Promotion Association and hosted by Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University was held in Xiamen on the same day.
The two well-known hospitals in Shanghai held the signing ceremony of the Vascular Surgery Collaboration Center at the same time of the meeting and announced the formation of a collaborative unit to jointly improve the level of treatment of vascular surgery-related diseases in southwest Fujian.
Vascular surgery at Shanghai Changhai Hospital is the only institute of vascular surgery in the army and the only clinical medical center for vascular system diseases in Shanghai. It is also the first national key discipline of vascular surgery. It has led the establishment of the Specialized Committee of Intra-Cavity Angiology of the Chinese Medical Association and is a well-established top team in the industry.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, was interviewed by the media.
Vascular surgery at Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University is the first vascular surgery set up by an independent discipline in Fujian Province, with a long-term commitment to the diagnosis and treatment of aortic and peripheral vascular diseases.
In the treatment of aortic diseases, in addition to the treatment of dissection aneurysms and aortic aneurysms, he has extensive experience in emergency ruptured aortic aneurysms.
" The vascular surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University is outstanding in this region in terms of the history of development, the breadth, difficulty and complexity of the operation. Therefore, this time we have set up a collaboration center. In addition to the aorta, we can also carry out in-depth cooperation in medicine, teaching and scientific research in the diagnosis and treatment of lower limb artery, carotid artery and other diseases. "
Professor Feng Rui, deputy director of vascular surgery at Shanghai Changhai Hospital, said.
Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University and Shanghai Changhai Hospital signed a contract to establish " Li Zhaoshen Famous Medical Studio " in the Department of Digestive Medicine in 2018.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, director of vascular surgery of the hospital, said in an interview with Xinhua News that the hospital's vascular surgery has also communicated with Changhai Hospital for a long time. This time, the two hospitals officially formed a collaborative unit, bringing the cooperation and exchanges between the two sides to a new level.
He said that the hospital will regularly invite Shanghai experts to the building to carry out surgical technical exchanges, teaching room inspection, difficult case discussion, etc. At the same time, it will further carry out remote consultation. At present, it plans to conduct remote consultation once a week. In addition, the department will also send personnel for further training and exchange to strengthen the training and development of disciplinary talents.
The reporter learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the leading cause of death in China, and that the aorta plays an important role as the main road of all human organs, flowing from the heart to the whole body.
The occurrence of aortic diseases is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality and high difficulty of treatment. The thickest section of the aorta is up to 4cm in diameter. Once a hemangioma is formed, rupture occurs, or the rupture of the intima of the blood vessels produces a dissection, it will cause large bleeding, which is very dangerous.
In recent years, with the change of people's lifestyle and the acceleration of the pace of life, China has become the largest country in the world with high blood pressure, and aortic diseases have also increased. Today, with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases has continued to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
Doctors can puncture from the thigh and place a stent in the aorta to properly " change the channel " of the blood flow, so as to avoid the impact of the aneurysm or ruptured dissection, and achieve good therapeutic results. Some operations even require local anesthesia.
The symposium invited more than 10 domestic experts to discuss the new progress in the treatment of aortic diseases, and conducted cutting-edge technical training and difficult case discussions in the form of a conference salon.
The reporter learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
