Longest high-speed railway tunnel through the Three Gorges Reservoir Area - New Network
2020-07-26 17: 34: 48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Executive Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Small Three Gorges Tunnel.
Photo of China Railway Chengdu Group Corporation
Xinhua News, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Group Co., Ltd. on July 26 that the Zheng-Wan High-Speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel, with a total length of 18.9 kilometers, was fully completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Small Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges reservoir area, but also the longest single-hole double-track high-speed railway tunnel designed to reach a speed of 350 km / h among the projects currently under construction in China.
The Zheng-Wan high-speed railway is located in the territory of the three provinces of Henan, Hubei and Chongqing. It connects the Beijing-Guangzhou and Xu Lan high-speed railway to the north of Zhengzhou and reaches Chongqing in the south of Wanzhou. It is an important part of the Yangtze River passageway and Huantong Road in China's " eight vertical and eight horizontal " high-speed railway network.
The Zheng-Wan High-Speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel was completed on the 26th.
The picture shows going through the scene.
The Zheng-Wan high-speed railway starts in Zhengzhou, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, Xiangyang City, Hubei Province to Wanzhou District, Chongqing. The new line has a total length of 818 km, with a design speed of 350 km / h, and about 184 km in Chongqing.
Among them, the section from Zhengzhou to Xiangyang was put into operation on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel, which runs through the entire line on the 26th, is a control project for the entire line of the Zheng-Wan high-speed railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing, with a total length of 18.9 kilometers and a maximum depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017 and was completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Jun, head of the Zheng Wan high-speed railway tunnel design of China Railway Eryuan Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the survey designer, the topography and geological conditions of the location of the Small Three Gorges Tunnel are very complex and face risks such as karst, mud inrush and large deformation of soft rock. It is a Class I high-risk tunnel, and the design and construction of the tunnel is extremely difficult.
" During the construction of the project, we made advance geological forecasts by means of geological survey, geophysical exploration and advanced drilling, and adopted special design plans for more than 30 karst caves of various types. For example, a bridge with a length of 24 meters was designed and built to cross large karst caves with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel subsidence, " the Royal Army said.
According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, the construction party of the tunnel adopted a combination of diversion and blockage during the construction of the tunnel, which not only ensured the orderly progress of the project, but also avoided the damage caused by construction drainage to the water bodies of the Small Three Gorges Scenic Area. At the same time, it successfully overcome construction problems such as unfavorable geology such as large deformation of soft rock up to 7 kilometers, and multi-mud flooding with a maximum daily inrush of 157,000 cubic meters.
When the entire line of the Zheng-Wan high-speed railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger route from southwest China to Central China, North China and Northeast China, which is of great significance for improving the capacity and quality of the southwest-northeast railway route, improving the layout of the regional road network, accelerating the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the route, promoting coordinated regional development and promoting the implementation of the western development strategy.
