The overall stability of employment and prices shows that the economy has a " temperature "
Economic Times · China Economic Network Journalist Lin Fo Chan
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic, China coordinated the work of epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development. The epidemic prevention and control situation was constantly improving, the steady economic recovery was evident, the performance of employment and prices closely related to people's livelihood was generally stable, and the Chinese economy handed over a warm economic performance report card.
The surveyed unemployment rate rose in the first two months of this year.
In particular, in February, the production and business activities of many enterprises were basically shut down, the demand for employment by enterprises was reduced, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the surveyed unemployment rate in cities and towns increased.
As the epidemic prevention and control situation has gradually improved, the production and living order of the whole society has been continuously restored.
The CPC Central Committee adheres to the general tone of the work of steady progress, further strengthens macro-policy hedging, comprehensively strengthens employment priority policies, and actively promotes the work of assisting and stabilizing jobs and expanding employment.
China has stepped up its policy of hedging and stabilizing jobs, launched a combination of policies of " reduction, reduction and slow return compensation, " phased reduction and reduction of the contributions paid by three social insurance units, allowed the postponement of the payment of social insurance premiums, expanded the scope of benefits from the unemployment insurance and job-for-work training policy for small and medium-sized enterprises, and provided absorption subsidies and internship subsidies to enterprises to absorb the employment of key groups.
With the implementation of various stable employment policies, the demand for employment by enterprises has steadily picked up, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the urban survey unemployment rate has gradually decreased. In June, the survey unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, director of the Department of Population and Employment Statistics of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to take effect, and the labor force who withdrew due to the impact of the epidemic gradually returned. The urban labor force participation rate in June increased by about 10 percentage points compared with February, which is close to the level of the same period last year.
The data show that the total number of urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached the pre-epidemic level. The average working hours of employees in enterprises reached 46.8 hours per week, 6.6 hours higher than in February and 0.1 hours higher than in January.
Prices also affect thousands of households.
In January, the CPI rose 5.4% year on year, a multi-year high.
In February, although the year-on-year increase in CPI fell slightly, it was still in the " 5 range. "
The year-on-year increase in CPI is at a high level, not only the pull factors of consumer demand before the Spring Festival, but also the wrong month of the Spring Festival and the lower year-on-year base.
However, the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on prices is particularly obvious.
Affected by the prevention and control of the epidemic, logistics delays, untimely material supplies and increased material transportation costs occurred in all parts of the country in January and February. In addition to some citizens hoarding and buying, the prices of some basic necessities increased significantly.
In order to cope with the disturbance caused by epidemic prevention and control to the price situation, the relevant departments have included important living materials in the scope of emergency transportation to ensure the smooth transportation of materials.
Under the effect of a series of policy measures, the supply of vegetables, melon and fruit market has been strongly guaranteed.
In order to cope with the rapid rise in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the Central Government issued the policy of stabilizing prices, various regions and departments quickly implemented the policy, the supply of pork reserves was significantly improved, the production capacity of pigs was restored in an orderly manner, and the order of production and marketing was gradually normal.
Pork prices have fallen continuously since March, and the year-on-year increase in food prices fell to 10.6% in May. In June, pork prices rose slightly due to factors such as the slowdown in the number of pigs, the reduction of imports and the recovery of group consumption demand.
The price of fresh vegetables has obvious seasonal characteristics, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the relatively high comparative base of the same period last year, the price of fresh fruit continued to decline year on year, with an average decline of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic livelihood of the masses has been effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation has remained stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation logistics, various places have increased their efforts, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Starting in March, the CPI fell for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase also fell from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to remain moderate, and the overall inflationary pressure is low, but we still need to promote the restoration of production and living order on the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
Effectively deal with natural disasters such as floods and droughts in major agricultural production areas such as grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on acts that disturb market order, such as hoarding and pushing up prices.
