In order to avoid the risks, Xiao Wen, Mr. Wen and many other children and parents moved in the safe area designated by the softball team.
But then softball team member Chen dropped off while throwing the ball, causing the softball to fly over the net to the above-mentioned safe area and hit Xiao Wen in the back of the head.
Mr. Wen immediately took Xiao Wen to the hospital for treatment and was diagnosed with a head injury.
Mr. Wen believed that the facilities of the school stadium did not comply with the relevant safety regulations and did not effectively manage the team and related facilities.
The negligence of the school led to the above-mentioned incident, which caused Xiao Wen to suffer great physical and mental suffering, but also brought great suffering to his family, for which the school should bear legal responsibility.
In this regard, the school argued that the school had set up a protective net in the playground and posted management regulations and training notices, informing them that entering the playground must maintain a safe distance from the training site and remind them of their own safety. The plaintiff could not prove that the school had " failed to fulfill its safety and security obligations, " so it did not agree to compensation.
After the hearing, the court held that the site of the incident was a site open to the public free of charge by the university involved. Although the school has a security obligation for the management of the playground, this security obligation only needs to meet the general duty of care.
At the time of the incident, the school set up a protective net in the playground and had fulfilled the appropriate security obligations, and Chen also compensated Xiao Wen more than 2,000 yuan for medical expenses, transportation expenses and other losses in accordance with the compensation agreement reached before. The two sides agreed to resolve the dispute at one time.
Later, Xiao Wen's parents again claimed the school compensation, which had no basis in the law, and the court decided to reject all the plaintiff's claims.
Following the judgement, neither party appealed, and the judgement has now entered into force.
According to the provisions of Article 37 of China's Tort Liability Law, schools, as administrators of public places, have the obligation of safety and security; if the actions of the third party cause damage to others, the third party shall bear the tort liability, while the administrators of public places who fail to fulfill the obligation of safety and security shall bear the corresponding supplementary liability.
The judge said that since, as the manager of a public place, he is most likely to know the actual situation of the whole place, foresee the danger and damage that may occur, and thus is most likely to take necessary measures to prevent the occurrence of the loss or mitigate the extent of the damage, and the cost of avoiding and mitigating the occurrence of the damage is the lowest, the law stipulates that he shall bear the corresponding guarantee obligation to engage in social activities.
In this case, for the non-specific people entering the playground open to the public free of charge, the school's safety and security obligations should be commensurate with its social activities. Specifically, it should take basic safety measures and have the obligation to inform of hidden dangers.
In judicial practice, it is also inappropriate to impose excessively high security obligations on the managers of public places.
If the school has set up a protective net and fulfilled its notification obligation, it can be concluded that the school is not at fault and should not bear legal responsibility.
In addition, for the infringement by a third party, even if the administrators of schools and other public places fail to fulfill their safety and security obligations, their liability is as a supplement to compensation for damages. According to the newly promulgated Civil Code, the administrators can also recover compensation from the third party after assuming the supplementary liability.
Therefore, in such accidents, the victim should not expand the scope of the claim after having received compensation from the direct infringer.
