Find out what is the professional grade difference before volunteering.
2020-07-27 02: 22: 36 Source: Chongqing Morning Post Author: Yu Xiao Editor: Yu Xiao
Find out what professional grade difference is before volunteering
Every year, there are students or parents who do not understand the terms involved in the voluntary application, which affects the voluntary application.
This year, five universities of Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing University of Chemical Technology jointly issued the 2020 admission policy, eliminating the professional grade difference.
What does professional grade difference mean and what is its significance in voluntary filing?
There are three ways of professional allocation rules
Experts reminded that before volunteering, you must carefully read the Admission Regulations of your favorite schools and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the adjustment ratio, professional allocation rules, etc.
Speciality allocation rules mean that after the adjustment of grades in colleges and universities, there are three main ways for professional admission: professional priority, score priority and professional grade difference.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be specified in the Admission Regulations.
However, the admission principle of some colleges and universities is that the total score is preferred, and there is no grade difference between majors.
In other words, candidates within the admission range will be queued according to the total score. When the score does not reach the voluntary admission line for the first major, it will see whether the voluntary admission line for the second major has been reached, and so on until the last professional volunteer is admitted, there is no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called " professional grade difference " means that institutions, when arranging candidates' specialties, determine the admission specialties of volunteer candidates for different specialties according to one or more points published in the admission regulations. This score value is the " professional grade difference. "
That is, the difference between the scores of the first professional volunteer and the non-first professional volunteer in the admission of candidates by colleges and universities, and the difference between the grades of volunteers in each major, such as 3, 2, 1, etc.
For example.
It is assumed that student Xiaoming applied for A University and scored 560 points, and his professional volunteers are as follows: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering and e-commerce. The professional admission of A University adopts the method of professional grade difference, and the grade difference is divided into 2, 1, 1 and 0.
At the time of professional allocation, if Xiaoming's volunteer for the first major meets the professional admission requirements and the major has a planned balance, then Xiaoming will be admitted to the " computer " major; if the computer is not accepted, his score will be reduced by 2 points, and the score of 558 points will be ranked with the candidates who volunteer for the " international trade " of the first major to determine whether they meet the professional admission requirements; if they still cannot be met, the score will be reduced by 1 point (i.e. 557 points) for the voluntary " automated " admission of the third major; if they still cannot be met, the score will be reduced by 1 point (i.e. 556 points) for the admission of the fourth major, and if the subsequent major is still unable to meet their professional volunteers, the score will not be reduced, and so on.
Different professional grade differences in different universities
With the popularization of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have now eliminated the professional grade difference, but some universities have retained this method this year. Judging from the Admissions Regulations published by each university, more than 20 universities have set up the professional grade difference this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Academy, etc.
In these universities, each university has a different professional grade difference.
Some colleges and universities have grade differences in each major, such as the University of Ningxia. The candidates whose files have been submitted to the university are admitted according to the order in which the candidates submit their professional volunteers by one point and then admitted according to the order of scores.
Some universities have set different professional grades between different majors.
For example, at Jimei University, the total grade difference between professional volunteers is 4 points, that is, the grade difference between first professional volunteers and other professional volunteers is 3 points, there is no grade difference between other professional volunteers, which is regarded as parallel volunteers, and the professional grade difference between other professional volunteers and transfer professional volunteers is 1 point.
When volunteering, candidates and their parents must carefully read the admission policies of the reported schools to see if there is any professional grade difference and what the form of grade difference is. While giving full consideration to the scores, they should also make a reasonable analysis of the schools and majors to be selected. If institutions clearly adopt the method of grade difference in their admission rules, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the various majors and improve the chances of admission.
